{"label":"Why Working with Models?", "tag":"tag", "type":"type", "category":"Thinking_BigComment", "size":"653 60", "key":401, "location":"2810 2930"},
{"text":"1) The problem at hand is too complex \n--- Working on it requires too much time/data/attention\n--- Difficult to visualise/introspect \n--- Difficult to debug/trace\n\n2) Repetition of similar tasks\n--- e.g. creating different design of a similar product\n--- Changing regularly one part of a system, make variations or product-line\n\n3) Simplify explanation for broader public\n--- Pedagogy: models as metaphors\n--- e.g. interactive simulations of complex system, interactive notebook, ...\n\n4) Democratisation of design or development\n--- No-Code: allowing non-specialist to make product\n\n5) Increase quality, productivity and affordability", "color":"Khaki", "figure":"Rectangle", "category":"Note_NodeType1", "size":"654 276", "key":402, "location":"2810 3099.8"},

{"label":"What are Models?", "tag":"tag", "type":"type", "category":"Thinking_BigComment", "size":"653 60", "key":407, "location":"1870 2590"},
{"text":"1) Models are simple conceptual representation of a subject\n--- e.g. a calendar is a model suitable for describing appointments over time\n--- e.g. a set of variable and equation can be a model for describing a physical process\n\n2) Models consists of concepts used to help people to:\n--- Explain, describe a subject\n--- Understand \n--- or simulate a subject\n\n3) Types of models can be:\n--- Data flow\n--- Entity-relationship\n--- Processes\n--- and more...\n", "color":"Khaki", "figure":"Rectangle", "category":"Note_NodeType1", "size":"654 276", "key":412, "location":"1870 2760"},

{"label":"Slide Scripts", "color":"plum", "size":"150 120", "category":"Hierarchy_CodeInGraph", "includeScript":true, "isFile":true, "fileContent":"/**\n * This function takes 2 parameters:\n * - direction: 'next'/'previous'\n * - nodeData: current slide toolbar nodeData\n * \n * This funtion move the view to the next/previous slide\n * if found, otherwise it goes to 'Slide 0'\n * \n */\nfunction navigateToSlide( direction, currSlideLabel ) {\n  // Get current slide number\n  const slideNumber = parseInt( currSlideLabel.split( ' ' )[1] );\n  //console.log( 'Number', slideNumber );\n  const ds = ( direction == 'Next'? 1: -1 );\n  // Set next slide label\n  const nextSlideLabel = `Slide ${slideNumber+ds}`;\n  \n  const dx = -50;\n  const dy = -50;\n  const found = setViewFromLabel( nextSlideLabel, dx, dy );\n  if( !found ) {\n    setViewFromLabel( 'Slide 0', dx, dy );\n  }\n}\n\nfunction jumpToSlide( targetSlideLabel ) {\n  const found = setViewFromLabel( targetSlideLabel, -100, -100 );\n  if( !found ) {\n    setViewFromLabel( 'Slide 1', -100, -100 );\n  } \n}\n\nfunction duplicateTemplateSlide( slideLabel ) {\n  // Get main graph\n  const g = getMainGraph();\n  \n  // Select slide template elements\n  const templateNodeKey = [ 368, 370, 372 ];\n  g.selectAllNodeByKey( templateNodeKey );\n  \n  // Create new slide\n  g.doEditDuplicate();\n  \n  // Set slide label\n  const firstNode = g.getFirstSelectedNodeData();\n  const firstNodeKey = firstNode.key;\n  g.setNodeDataField( firstNodeKey, 'label', slideLabel );\n  g.moveSelectionRel( 900, 0 );\n}", "fileTypeName":"Javascript", "fileType":"text/javascript", "key":490, "location":"580 -1980"},
